Steps.Message: Update at 12:17 - We can now confirm that all power in the London Road area should be back on. Our engineers have made partial repairs to our underground cabling, bringing power back to the majority of customers. However, due to the location and complexity of the issue, we have also used temporary generator to restore power to the last of the affected properties. Our engineers have advised they may need to disconnect power for a few minutes while safety checks are carried out. This will provide power until our engineers plan in and safely complete the full repair, which may take a few days. We're really sorry for any disruption this caused. If your power isn't on or there's anything you'd like to talk to us about, call us on 08003163105 which is free from landlines and mobiles.

We became aware of this power cut at 23:38. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
Steps.Name: Engineers on their way

Steps.Message: Engineers are now on site, carrying out investigations into the fault. Once they have completed their assessment, they will carry out repairs.
Steps.Name: Engineers investigating and fixing

Steps.Message: All power in the area should be back on. We’re really sorry for any disruption this caused.
Steps.Name: Power restored
